<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[131,775,974,1384]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
DISTRIBUTION AND HABITAT. — 
<taxonomicName box="[447,681,1334,1358]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inappendiculata">
<emphasis box="[447,681,1334,1358]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Scolopia inappendiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in dry forest in northwestern Madagascar (
<figureCitation box="[523,579,1360,1384]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[812,823,1261,1279]" captionTargetBox="[811,1457,213,1220]" captionTargetId="figure-752@10.[804,1465,195,1225]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Distributions of S. inappendiculata H.Perrier (★), S. madagascariensis Sleumer (●), S. manongarivae H.Perrier (■), and S. spinescens Sleumer (▲)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4598929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4598929/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), on sand.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[130,777,1428,1613]" box="[132,232,1428,1454]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[130,777,1428,1613]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName box="[132,395,1459,1485]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inappendiculata">
<emphasis box="[132,395,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Scolopia inappendiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small tree or large shrub with platanoid bark. It is the only species found around Mahajanga, and is distinguished from species of the xerophytic group known from the extreme north by its larger, often shortacuminate leaves and few or absent spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="109" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="10.[131,775,1652,2028]" box="[132,379,1652,1678]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">CONSERVATION STATUS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[131,775,1652,2028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
The preliminary assessment of the conservation status of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inappendiculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Scolopia inappendiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is Endangered (EN B1ab(iii)+B2ab(iii)). It is known from at most four locations in the region of Mahajanga, with an Extent of Occurrence of 
<quantity box="[622,718,1778,1804]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.161" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" unit="km" value="1161.0">1161 km</quantity>
2 and a minimum Area of Occupancy of 
<quantity box="[522,595,1810,1836]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" unit="km" value="16.0">16 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[595,605,1811,1828]" fontSize="7" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">2</superScript>
; the maximum potential Area of Occupancy is certainly less than 
<quantity box="[681,765,1841,1868]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" unit="km" value="500.0">500 km</quantity>
2 given that much of the area within the EOO polygon consists of the delta of the Betsiboka River. The species has not been recollected for almost fifty years, despite the accessible terrain, and the limited remaining natural vegetation in the area is subject to continuing habitat degradation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
